subject: Science
question: Question: The development of science has been intertwined with that of its hokey brother, pseudoscience. For 10 points each, name some historical examples of quackery. [10] This quack discipline invented by Samuel Hahnemann employs insanely highly diluted substances. Its so-called remedies often lack any molecules of the compounds they claim to contain.
